{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = Amb. |name = Gina Ama Blay |honorific-suffix = |image = |imagesize = |smallimage = <!--If this is specified, "image" should not be.--> |alt = |caption = |order = |office = Ambassador to Germany |term_start = June 2017 |term_end = |president = [[Nana Akuffo-Addo]] |predecessor = |successor = ''Incumbent'' |birth_date = 29 Ootober 1956 |birth_place = [[Ghana]] |death_date = |death_place = |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality = [[Ghanaian]] |party = [[New Patriotic Party]] |otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> |spouse = [[Freddie Blay]] |relations = Husband |children = |residence = |alma_mater = [[University of Ghana]] |occupation = |profession = |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |religion = |signature = |signature_alt = |website = |footnotes = |blank1 = |data1 = |blank2 = |data2 = |blank3 = |data3 = |blank4 = |data4 = |blank5 = |data5 = }}
'''Gina Blay''' (born 29 October 1956)<ref name="battle"/> is a [[Ghanaian]] journalist and diplomat and a sympathizer of the [[New Patriotic Party]] of Ghana. She is currently Ghana's ambassador to Germany.<ref name="sta">{{cite web|last1=Online|first1=Starrfm|title=Ambassadors list|url=http://starrfmonline.com/2017/03/17/ambassadors-list-gina-blay-for-germany-anna-bossman-for-france/|website=starrfmonline.com/|publisher=starrfmonline|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="jonas"/>
==Educational life== Gina Blay obtained her [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree from the [[University of Ghana]].<ref name="battle"/>
==Working life== Gina Blay is the [[Chief Executive Officer]] of Western Publication Limited a print media house. The main publication of the house is [[Daily Guide (Ghana)|Daily Guide]] Newspaper.<ref name="battle"/>
==Battle with cancer== She was diagnosed with breast cancer in 2008 and had series of [[chemotherapy]] treatment.<ref name="battle">{{cite web|last1=FM Online|first1=Ultimate|title=I Am A Cancer Survivor – Gina Blay|url=https://www.modernghana.com/news/724812/i-am-a-cancer-survivor-gina-blay.html|website=modernghana.com|publisher=modernghana|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>
==Ambassadorial appointment== In June 2017, [[Nana Akuffo-Addo|President Nana Akuffo-Addo]] named Gina Blay as Ghana's ambassador to [[Germany]]. She was among eight other distinguished Ghanaians who were named to head various Ghanaian diplomatic missions in the world.<ref name="jonas">{{cite web|last1=Nyabor|first1=Jonas|title=Ayikoi Otoo, Gina Blay, 5 others given ambassadorial roles|url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/03/17/ayikoi-otoo-gina-blay-5-others-given-ambassadorial-roles/|website=citifmonline.com|publisher=citifmonline|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="moyhjoy">{{cite web|last1=Online|first1=Myjoy|title=Akufo-Addo swears in first batch of 8 Ambassadors|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/politics/2017/June-3rd/akufo-addo-swears-in-first-batch-of-8-ambassadors.php|website=myjoyonline.com|publisher=myjoyonline|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>
==Personal life== Gina Blay is married to the acting National Chairman of the New Patriotic Party, [[Freddie Blay]].<ref name="STARJM">{{cite web|last1=Online|first1=StarFM|title=I’m not NPP - Gina Blay|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/I-m-not-NPP-Gina-Blay-475096|website=ghanaweb.com|publisher=ghanaweb|accessdate=16 July 2017}}</ref>
