'''Microsoft Planner''' is a planning application available on the Microsoft [[Office 365]] platform. The application is available to premium, business, and educational subscribers to Office 365.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ben |last=Lovejoy |url=http://9to5mac.com/2016/06/07/microsoft-planner-office-365/ |title=Microsoft offers new Planner app to 'eligible' Office 365 subscribers |website=9to5Mac |accessdate=June 7, 2016}}</ref>

On June 6, 2016 [[Microsoft]] made the application available for general release and intends to roll it out over coming weeks to eligible subscription plans.<ref>{{cite web |first=Sarah |last=Perez |url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/06/06/microsoft-officially-launches-planner-its-trello-competitor |title=Microsoft officially launches Planner, its Trello competitor |website=TechCrunch |publisher=[[Aol]] |accessdate=June 6, 2016}}</ref>

Planner enables users and teams to create plans, assemble and assign tasks, share files, communicate and collaborate with other users, and receive progress updates via various means on the Office 365 platform. Each new plan created in Planner automatically creates a new Office 365 group.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.office.com/2016/06/06/microsoft-planner-ready-for-showtime |title=Microsoft Planner ready for showtime |website=Office Blog |publisher=Microsoft |accessdate=June 6, 2016}}</ref>

