'''Paul Borghgraef''' (born 13 July 1954) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. He is a son of Theo Borghgraef and Suzanne Collin, who is a daughter of [[Fernand Collin]]. He is a member of the board of directors of the [[KBC Group]].

==Early life==
He obtained a degree in [[Accounting]] and Fiscal Studies and a [[postgraduate degree]] in [[computer science]] and [[legislation|social legislation]] from the ''Economische Hogeschool'' in [[Antwerp]]. 

==Career==
He was formerly [[Managing Director]] of [[Krefima]] and [[Concentra]], and Director of [[KBC Bank|Kredietbank S.A. Luxembourgeoise]]. He is Chairman of the Board of Directors of Retail Estates. He was appointed Director of [[Almanij]] in 2000 and became a member of its Management Committee in 2001. When in 2005, Almanij merged with KBC to form the KBC Group, he became a member of the board of the new group.<ref>{{cite web|title=Raad van bestuur nieuwe KBC Groep |url=http://www.standaard.be/Artikel/Detail.aspx?artikelId=gnqcpfhg&kanaalid=42|publisher=[[De Standaard]]|accessdate=20 December 2010|language=Dutch|date=24 February 2005}}</ref>

