'''Ryutaro Nomura''' ({{lang-ja|野村龍太郎}}) (February 27, 1859 – September 18, 1943) was a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] businessman. He was born in [[Gifu Prefecture]]. He was a graduate of the [[University of Tokyo]]. He was twice President of the [[South Manchuria Railway]] (1913–1914, 1919–1921). He was a recipient of the [[Order of the Sacred Treasure]] and the [[Order of the Rising Sun]].

